N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 8 ยง 73.4 - Laboratories

State Regulations

Pursuant to section
6551
(3)
of the Education Law, a licensee may use
for diagnostic purposes those clinical laboratory services which are contained
within the required coursework of all registered doctoral programs in
chiropractic in this State and the study of which the licensee has successfully
completed in a course of study satisfactory to the department, provided that
nothing herein contained shall be construed as expanding the definition of the
practice of chiropractic. Notes
